_time_extracted.description: Time at which report was extracted

provider.description: Service provider in your reports (typically Apple).

sku.description: Product identifier provided by you during app setup.

developer.description: Provider name provided by you during the initial account setup.

title.description: App name provided by you during app setup.

version.description: Version number provided by you during app setup.

product_type_identifier.description: Defines the type of transaction (for example, initial download or update)

units.description: Aggregated number of units. Negative values indicate refunds, or CMB credits for previously purchased apps when the CMB column shows CMB-C. A value of 0 may indicate a partial refund.

developer_proceeds.description: Amount you receive per unit. This is the customer price minus applicable taxes and Apple’s commission, per Schedule 2 of your Paid Applications Agreement.

customer_currency.description: Three-character ISO code indicating the customer’s currency

country_code.description: Two-character ISO country code indicating the App Store storefront through which the purchase was made

currency_of_proceeds.description: The currency in which the customer is paid

customer_price.description: The price per unit billed to the customer, which you set for your app or in-app purchase in App Store Connect

promo_code.description: If the transaction was part of a promotion, this field will contain a value. This field is empty for all non-promotional items

parent_identifier.description: SKU of the app associated with the in-app purchase

subscription.description: Defines whether an auto-renewable subscription is new or a renewal. When a previous subscriber resubscribes, it's classified as a renewal

period.description: Defines the duration of an auto-renewable subscription purchase: 7 days, 1 month, 2 months, 3 months, 6 months, and 1 year

category.description: Indicates the primary category of the app, such as Games

cmb.description: If the transaction completes an app bundle, this field will contain a value of “CMB.” App credits for completed bundles will show a value of “CMB-C.” Otherwise this field is blank

device.description: Type of device used for purchase or redownload: iPhone, iPad, Apple TV, iPod touch, or Desktop

supported_platforms.description: List of platforms that your app supports: iOS, tvOS, iOS and tvOS, or macOS

proceeds_reason.description: If a subscription is active for more than a year, you receive 85% of the customer price (minus applicable taxes) and this field equals “Rate After One Year”. Otherwise, you receive 70% and the field is blank.

preserved_pricing.description: For Renew events, if the price is preserved then this field equals “Yes”. Otherwise, it’s blank

client.description: Indicates where the purchase happened: App Store for iMessage, News, or blank.

order_type.description: For introductory or subscription offers, displays the type of transaction: Pay Up Front or Pay As You Go. For pre-orders, indicates whether a purchase originated from a pre-order. For promotional offers, displays the order ID. For offer codes, displays the offer code reference name you entered in App Store Connect when setting up the subscription offer
